Package elpasominersbank

package elpasominersbank
  • Class
    Description
    Account
    Represents a bank account.
    BankDatabase
    Represents the bank's database, which manages the collection of customer by loading data from the a CSV file, and updating the customer's data to the file.
    Checking
    Represents a checking account.
    Credit
    Represents a credit account.
    Customer
    Represents a type of person called bank customer.
    CustomerFactory
    Factory class for creating new Customer objects with associated accounts.
    DesignDeposit
    Implements computation to perform a deposit.
    DesignTransfer
    Implementation for a transfer from one account to another.
    DesignWithdraw
    Implementation of the withdraw functionality for accounts.
    Interaction
    The Interaction interface provides methods for selecting accounts, performing transactions, and interacting with a banking system.
    InterfaceDeposit
    Interface to represent strategy design pattern to perform a deposit.
    InterfaceTransfer
    Interface to represent strategy design pattern to perform a transfer.
    InterfaceWithdraw
    Interface to represent strategy design pattern to perform a withdraw.
    LogFile
    Helps to keep track of all transactions
    ManagerInteraction
    Handles manager interactions, such as creating customers, inquiring about accounts, and processing transactions.
    Person
    This class represents a general person, with attributes such as first name, last name, date of birth, and address
    PersonInteraction
    Handles customer interactions, such as viewing balances, depositing money, transferring funds, and authenticating users.
    RunBank
    The RunBank class represents the banking system of El Paso Miners Bank.
    Saving
    Represents a saving account.
